-- Mexico Raises 2010 Growth Forecast to 4.8 Percent from 4.5 Percent
-- B y   J e n s   E r i k   G o u l d
-- 2010-10-20T23:30:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/mexico-raises-2010-growth-forecast-to-4-8-percent-from-4-5-percent.html
Mexico’s economy will grow 4.8
percent in 2010, Finance Minister Ernesto Cordero said in Mexico
City today. The government’s previous growth forecast was 4.5
percent.  The Mexican economy added 58,569 formal jobs in the first
half of October, Labor Minister Javier Lozano said, speaking at
the same event.  To contact the reporter on this story:
